headline.main: Arrest of an Irish Girl for Setting on Fire a Catholic Church--Discharge of James McDonald, Claimed under the Ashburton Treaty--Decision of Judge Phelps, &c.

docs.lead_paragraph: ELLEN KEENAN, a young Irish girl, has been arrested in Watertown, for setting on fire a Catholic Church in that place. She is reported to have had some difficulty with the priest.

docs.lead_paragraph: By the Union, which arrived early this morning, bringing tour days later news from Europe, we receive full particulars of the Russian sortie of Nov. 5. The confliet was even more severe, and the loss to allies greater than was previously stated, Four English Generals were killed and four wounded.

docs.lead_paragraph: By the arrival of the United States mail steamship Union, Captaion ADAM, we have jates from Ham of the Rist, and Southampton and London to the 23rd up. The Union State mail steamship Washingtion, Captain CAVERLY, arrived off Cowes on hor way to Brenen on the 19th The Oonard steamship Niagara, from Boston and Halifax, reached Liverpoot the same day.

headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY; TRIAL FOR DIVORCE. SUPERIOR COURT.

docs.lead_paragraph: One of Franeen L. China vs. Solomon Childs. SUPREME COURT-CIRCUIT. Before Hialton, Jadge Roosevelt. EIGHTH DAY.. THURSDAY, Dec. 7 The Court room was full at the time of the opening of Court, and before 11 o'clock all of the available space outside of the bar was occupied by spectators, seated and standing.
